        "Bachelor of Science in Accounting": [
            "Bachelor of Science in Accounting The Bachelor of Science in Accounting requires the common core of the College of Business courses. Courses within the accounting major provide students with a broad understanding of accounting theory and practice, incorporating and infusing data analytics, information technology, and ethical issues. The program prepares students for a diversified range of career opportunities and meets the requirements to sit for the Certified Public Accountant (CPA) Examination, as well as the Certified Management Accountant (CMA) Examination and the Certified Internal Auditor (CIA) Examination. Students working toward a Bachelor of Science in Accounting must achieve a 2.00 grade point average overall as well as a 2.50 grade point average in the Business core and accounting concentration to graduate."
        ],
        "Rowan Core: 9 s.h.": {
